	Document(content="""Question: Is CNN on the exam tomorrow? Convolutional Neural Networks? Answer: Yes, CNN is under the Neural Networks. So it might be on the exam tomorrow. """, meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Syllabus for exam', 'timestamp': '2023-05-04T21:42:45Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 188}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>Could someone please explain the damage questions? Thank you</p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fl6maptmggzy7op%2F52da793480633012ef86311b74d41fa47a222ddb36a0ee71736b88373fb7560c%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p> Answer: For Question 1 - <br />The warrior attacks the player. The player has 20 health, 11 power and 10 armor. The warrior has 20 power, 15 armor. The base damage dealt will be - (20 - 10) = 10 - look at the attack() function in the PlayerCharacter class since it has not been overridden by the warrior class. The target has 20 health, so their final health is going to be their health - incoming damage = 10 health. Therefore, the print statement will be what is in the options. <br /><br />For Q2 - <br />The barbarian has 12 armor with 40 health. The wizard has 10 health, 20 power, 5 armor. The wizard attacks the barbarian - look at the attack() function in the wizard class; since the barbarian has 12 armor, the power of the wizard is doubled. The base damage dealt will be (40 - 12) = 28. The barbarian takes half of that damage - i.e. 14 damage. So the print statement will be the one in option B.""", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Fall 2022 Question 2 Part B', 'timestamp': '2023-05-04T01:51:57Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 149}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb5b8oexj1jg%2F35081b93587b452a0b06fd98faa9d349788fd8c8fc25115ada2d41a0297b76df%2Fimage.png' alt='image.pngNaN' /></p><p>Is there a slide covering BIC value? I couldn&#39;t seem to find it.</p> Answer: It was presented in the gmms_notebook, so you should read up on BIC and AIC model selection criteria there.""", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'BIC value', 'timestamp': '2023-05-04T01:47:58Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 132}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb76ph3se4g2%2Fc7c1ddedb9590a840824f4d133666bea0b121ac2d3d0962d5a9a0fa556a8e00d%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p><p></p><p>How does one compute the (1- 0.5) parts and is it always (1- 0.5), since that was what it was in both exams?</p> Answer: Please refer to @686 for the complete explanation.""", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'loss function', 'timestamp': '2023-05-04T01:08:40Z', 'user': 'ktnb76ph3se4g2', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 120}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb5b8oexj1jg%2F8577588c5d38281414ac3cb4512b50ed8905b16934236fdfbd786e72cc8b258c%2Fimage.png' alt='image.pngNaN' /></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb5b8oexj1jg%2F3ec99cc01012a10d467d8a0cb14e164c7eec2ff86b534eaacf62917139775e82%2Fimage.png' alt='image.pngNaN' /></p><p>Is Warrior not a correct answer because __init__ is not a functionality? If so, what are considered functionality?</p> Answer: The question asks for the classes that override any methods of the parent class (any of the functions that are not the constructors for that class)""", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'fall 2022 exam3 q2a', 'timestamp': '2023-05-04T00:47:47Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 119}),
