	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb8glb4hz3ee%2F2f208d419013306e9c78a70cc3296deae72dbea4ee9addbad74ab99eebad00aa%2FScreenshot_2023-04-28_at_8.20.28_PM.png' width='1312' height='80' alt='' /></p><p>I tried getting the &#39;Day&#39; part of the csv file by doing this but I knew it wasn&#39;t right since pandas.to_numeric gets the number but not a string, so I was wondering what I can do to use &#39;Day&#39;? This is for step 3 by the way and I am trying both Kmeans and regression to see which one shows more accurate data.</p> Answer: You actually don&#39;t have to do any more preprocessing for the Day column and you can use it as is. If you want to convert the days of the week to numbers (if that makes it easier for you), you&#39;d have to do that manually.""", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Path 2 panda.to_numeric question', 'timestamp': '2023-04-29T00:22:18Z', 'user': 'ktnb8glb4hz3ee', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 11}),
