	Document(content="""Note: I recieved a lot of questions during office hours on path 3 regarding the PCA. Just wanted to point out a few things:<br /><br />The link in the ReadMe is a great resource: <a href='https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/applications/plot_digits_denoising.html'>Image denoising using kernel PCA — scikit-learn 1.2.2 documentation</a><br /><br />Make sure to read the section under &#34;Learn the PCA basis&#34; and &#34;reconstruct and denoise test images&#34;. I have also see some students play around with the parameters of the PCA to get different results. for example, you can change the value of n_components to another value other than 400, or even &#39;None&#39;.""", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Hint on Denoising for Path 3', 'timestamp': '2023-04-28T21:23:10Z', 'user': 'kskmxecspaq4i1', 'tags': ['instructor-note', 'project'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 132}),
