	Document(content="""Question: <p>for the following function,</p><pre>dataset_searcher(number_list, images, labels):</pre><p></p><p>how should I approach for this one?</p><p></p><p>I tried to use the below function, but it basically accepts one parameter and I&#39;m not sure how to find image and labels?</p><pre>sklearn.datasets.load_digits()</pre> Answer: You don&#39;t have to use sklearn.datasets.load_digits(). If you look at the top of the file, they already load the data for you. You just have to find images with the labels they pass into the function. You can use a selection structure to find images that match the labels passed into the function. """, meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'mini project path 3 step 1 question', 'timestamp': '2023-04-22T00:10:48Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 105}),
