	Document(content="""Question: <p>Hi,</p><p>I&#39;m a bit confused about problem 1, what would the values be in the confusion matrix? And how would we use the true classes label list?</p><p>Thanks</p> Answer: <p>The confusion matrix is a matrix that compares predicted values of the model to actual values. The values along the diagonal from the top left to the bottom right are the correct predictions that your model makes, and all the other values are incorrect predictions.</p><p></p><p>For example:</p><p>15, 3, 1</p><p>2, 12, 3</p><p>2, 2, 10</p><p></p><p>The model that resulted in the matrix above made 37 (15 &#43; 12 &#43; 10) correct predictions and 13 (3 &#43; 1 &#43; 2 &#43; 3 &#43; 2 &#43; 2) incorrect predictions.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw10'], 'title': 'Problem 1 conf_matrix() function what would the values be in the confusion matrix?', 'timestamp': '2023-04-21T00:23:58Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw10', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 9}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fk5b7odaxv6v3sw%2Fbcc35e9cf077ccdd6235c6cce8fec52d7e79e4b19cd4d78c45bdc49e2bd7127c%2FScreenshot_2023-04-20_at_5.57.05_PM.png' alt='' width='700' height='1022' /></p><p></p><p>I&#39;m getting the correct output, but I get the following error :</p><p>ConvergenceWarning: Stochastic Optimizer: Maximum iterations (200) reached and the optimization hasn&#39;t converged yet.<br /><br /></p><p>Also, is it normal to take more than 2 minutes to get SVM and MLP results? Mine currently takes ~2 minutes to get the SVM, MLP results with warning.</p><p></p> Answer: As stated in the Readme, if your outputs match, you can ignore the warning, and yes, it&#39;s typical to get those times with SVM and the MLP models.""", meta={'folders': ['hw10'], 'title': 'HW10 ConvergenceWarning', 'timestamp': '2023-04-20T22:01:12Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw10', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 98}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fkeprehh4rvj2uc%2F006e8ae30c5c703fde062504d953a7f2d3c388260169871c5fa54b272e79af19%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p><p></p><p><a href='https://github.com/ECEDataScience/homework-10-s23-richa547' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>https://github.com/ECEDataScience/homework-10-s23-richa547</a></p><p></p><p>My code works for the accuracy score and accuracy but my confusion matrix doesn&#39;t show like in the readme. Is there something wrong in my confusion matrix function?</p><p></p> Answer: Yes. Because of how confusion matrixes are generated, the sum of the contents of your confusion matrixes should be equal to the length of the y_pred and y_true lists. """, meta={'folders': ['hw10'], 'title': 'Confusion Matrix Not Working', 'timestamp': '2023-04-20T21:49:22Z', 'user': 'keprehh4rvj2uc', 'tags': ['hw10', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 11}),
