	Document(content="""Question: <p>When I try to run my code  the error ModuleNotFoundError: No module named &#39;tkinter&#39; appears. I&#39;ve tried to use pip to download tkinter but it fails to find a suitable version with the error below. I&#39;ve tried to pip install using Tkinter and tkinter. EDIT: I have tried to update pip but that fails. tkinter is not used in my code but it seems to be required for matplotlib</p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb57ll3pzvw%2F7494f525dfa77200979ca37ffb9b4a66b305dfb3837d3fdebada47b512b609fb%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p> Answer: You seem to be using an old version of pip which might cause issues in installing different packages. Try upgrading pip by doing:<div>pip install --user --upgrade pip </div><div>OR</div><div>python3 -m pip install pip --user --upgrade</div><div><br /></div><div>If upgrading pip and reinstalling your package does not work, I would try:</div><div>apt-get install python3-tk </div><div>instead of installing it using pip.</div>""", meta={'folders': ['hw10'], 'title': 'Tkinter import error', 'timestamp': '2023-04-20T18:59:42Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw10', 'student'], 'likes': 2, 'views': 95}),
