	Document(content="""Question: <p><a href='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb5alnvkt1g6%2F4efe24c16920a866c961ce6dc693d997c9feb09f1d69d19fddd22451fe527f2b%2FScreenshot_2023-04-17_131105.png' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>S<img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb5alnvkt1g6%2F4efe24c16920a866c961ce6dc693d997c9feb09f1d69d19fddd22451fe527f2b%2FScreenshot_2023-04-17_131105.png' width='495' height='295' alt='' /></a></p><p>All my results are exactly the same except for the auc score which is slightly off every time. Is simply due to rounding? If that is the case I will simply ignore it and move on, if not however I would like to fix it!</p> Answer: <p><br />I’m not certain, but I think your result is off enough that it is likely not due to rounding — rounding issues usually manifest after around 10 decimal places. </p><div></div><div>Add: I have seen someone having slightly off results because of the machine (OS) it runs on, the version of Python, and the version of modules. You may try your code on eceprog /scholar clute</div><div></div><p></p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw10'], 'title': 'Auc score slightly off', 'timestamp': '2023-04-17T17:12:33Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw10', 'student'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 139}),
