	Document(content="""Question: <p>I have written the code for distFrom in point.py. How do I implement that into cluster.py? Do I have to re-calculate it? </p><p></p><p>Thank you!</p><p></p><pre> sum_sq = 0 # Initialize sum of squares to 0        i = 0 # index variable        while i &lt; self.dim:            sum_sq &#43;= (self.coords[i] - other.coords[i]) ** 2 # Subtract coordinates and square it            i &#43;= 1        distance = math.sqrt(sum_sq) # Calculate the square root        return distance</pre><p></p><p></p> Answer: Okay, I think I figured it out. I forgot about Point.distFrom. """, meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'how do we use our distFrom function in cluster.py?', 'timestamp': '2023-04-14T02:25:04Z', 'user': 'ktnb68csasm6k1', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 10}),
