	Document(content="""Question: <p>My lowest bic is corresponding with k = 6, when I print out the bic score it seems to be the correct value as well. Is there possible something wrong with something else earlier in my code?</p><p>Below is my code.</p><div><div></div></div><p><a href='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fkeprehh4rvj2uc%2Facf9173ca05d98f932e26b893ebf15c9cdc695affb531285f37a279cb10c3f64%2Fgmm.py' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>gmm.py</a></p> Answer: Your &#39;<kbd>gaus_mixture</kbd>&#39; function looks correct. In your code, you set <kbd>n = len(X1)</kbd> and still use the same n to reshape <kbd>X2</kbd>. You may want to check that.""", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'Problem 2 Bic', 'timestamp': '2023-04-13T03:13:21Z', 'user': 'keprehh4rvj2uc', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 11}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>Hi, I&#39;m working on the cluster part of hw 9, and I&#39;m getting a weird error. </p><p></p><p>Here&#39;s my code and the output:</p><pre>def avgDistance(self):	sum_of_dist = 0  	for pt in self.points:    	sum_of_dist &#43;= self.center.distFrom(pt)  avg_dist = sum_of_dist / (len(self.points))  return avg_distdef updateCenter(self):	if (len(self.points) != 0):  	self.center = self.avgDistance  returnOutput:Cluster: 0 points and center = [0.5, 3.5]Cluster: 2 points and center = [0.5, 3.5]1.4976761962286425Cluster: 2 points and center = 1.4976761962286425Traceback (most recent call last):  File &#34;/home/shay/a/nkap/homework-9-s23-nathankap/cluster.py&#34;, line 97, in &lt;module&gt;    print(c.avgDistance)  File &#34;/home/shay/a/nkap/homework-9-s23-nathankap/cluster.py&#34;, line 41, in avgDistance    sum_of_dist &#43;= self.center.distFrom(pt)AttributeError: &#39;float&#39; object has no attribute &#39;distFrom&#39;</pre><div></div><div>Which is weird because the first avgDistance function works fine, but the second one isn&#39;t. Any help would be appreciated</div> Answer: In your <kbd>avgDistance</kbd> function, it seems you are not updating the <kbd>sum_of_dist</kbd> correctly. You should be calculating the distance from all points which is called <kbd>pt</kbd> in your case to the center. I think you have it reversed.""", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'AttributeError', 'timestamp': '2023-04-13T01:54:26Z', 'user': 'ktnb533c31sbi', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 12}),
