	Document(content="""Question: <p>Is it alright if I am getting long decimals for my cluster center when running kmeans.py?</p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb7hcvqm46hd%2F2fd4b8b13fff5d195078cd323507d2b16d074034d44ea73ddbcfc1d42557922e%2FScreen_Shot_2023-04-09_at_11.37.20_AM.png' width='539' height='130' alt='' /></p> Answer: Yes, that&#39;s fine - this is because of floating point arithmetic (the 0.75000000001 and so on).""", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'HW9 Kmeans', 'timestamp': '2023-04-09T15:40:15Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 167}),
