	Document(content="""Question: <p>I filled in my functions for problem 1, but the output is being a little weird. Comparing it to the given test case, it&#39;s missing some nchars and their values and I&#39;m not sure why. Based on looking at each loop individually, it seems like the problem lies somewhere in my get_dict() function instead of the top_common_N. Any help would be appreciated</p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb533c31sbi%2F51b66eb24c7492208655a5b41788d2ba3107df538df838303ff3d0e42406ebdd%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p> Answer: <p>Nevermind, I found out the problem. When making my list of ngrams, I needed to make it ngrams &#43;= get_ngrams instead of just =</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'HW8 Problem 1', 'timestamp': '2023-03-31T00:31:40Z', 'user': 'ktnb533c31sbi', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 14}),
