	Document(content="""Question: <p>When checking the top_N_common function using</p><pre>    print(top_N_common(path, 20, 4))</pre><p>in the main, do we have to print the following as stated in the github?</p><pre>{&#39; the&#39;: 126, &#39;the &#39;: 119, &#39;and &#39;: 106, &#39; and&#39;: 106, &#39; of &#39;: 89, &#39;tion&#39;: 88, &#39; to &#39;: 84, &#39;atio&#39;: 61, &#39;ion &#39;: 58, &#39;righ&#39;: 54, &#39;ight&#39;: 54, &#39; rig&#39;: 54, &#39;one &#39;: 43, &#39; in &#39;: 42, &#39;all &#39;: 39, &#39;e ri&#39;: 36, &#39;very&#39;: 35, &#39;t to&#39;: 34, &#39;s th&#39;: 34, &#39;ght &#39;: 34}</pre><p>Or is it okay to output this instead?</p><pre>{&#39; the&#39;: 126, &#39;the &#39;: 119, &#39;and &#39;: 106, &#39; and&#39;: 106, &#39; of &#39;: 89, &#39;tion&#39;: 88, &#39; to &#39;: 84, &#39;atio&#39;: 61, &#39;ion &#39;: 58, &#39; rig&#39;: 54, &#39;ight&#39;: 54, &#39;righ&#39;: 54, &#39;one &#39;: 43, &#39; in &#39;: 42, &#39;all &#39;: 39, &#39;e ri&#39;: 36, &#39;very&#39;: 35, &#39;t to&#39;: 34, &#39;s th&#39;: 34, &#39;ght &#39;: 34}</pre> Answer: <p>No, the function definition clearly specifies to output the frequency dictionary.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'Checking top_N_common function', 'timestamp': '2023-03-29T22:53:34Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 139}),
