	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb3vlkh772ks%2F86a2c5685381a468dadb9f7c5c29b967df65867e112976d7670b505f58a3410b%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p><p>Based on the output for the first test case, we should have different values for for the nt values of the first 4 ngrams in our array of ngrams (specifically they should be 1 1 2 2). However, their outputs in the idf matrix are the same even though the nt values that would be used in the formula for idf should be different. Is this a mistake in the README or is there something Im missing here?</p> Answer: <p>Nvm, realized nT measures the # of documents something appears in and not just the total count of appearances.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'HW8 Potential Readme error?', 'timestamp': '2023-03-29T01:30:51Z', 'user': 'ktnb3vlkh772ks', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 151}),
