	Document(content="""Question: <p>I tested the code I wrote for top_N_common and get_dict, and I get what is practically the correct output. However, if the frequency of some n-grams are equivalent, the n-grams are put in a different order. I attached a screenshot below.</p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb5dhj6nu1up%2Fe41995a0bf3cc6fe4e0893c37807623ba691c800c510c142288877d3fcb14b44%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p><p>In the readme, the order is &#39;righ&#39;, &#39;ight&#39;, &#39; rig&#39;. Will this be an issue?</p> Answer: <p>You need to first sort the dictionary of all the n-grams, first with respect to values (high-to-low) and if their values turn out same then by their keys (characters), with the same ordering policy as you used for the keys (high-to-low), then return a dictionary containing the top N elements (key, value).</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'top_N_common output slightly different', 'timestamp': '2023-03-25T15:52:50Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 150}),
