	Document(content="""Question: <p>RuntimeWarning: overflow encountered in power return _nx.power(base, y)</p><p>ValueError: setting an array element with a sequence. The requested array has an inhomogeneous shape after 1 dimensions. The detected shape was (8311,) &#43; inhomogeneous part.</p><p></p><p>What does this mean? I&#39;m trying to fit the ridge regression and I&#39;m getting this error.</p> Answer: <p>I ran into a similar error. It&#39;s probably an error in the logspace function. If you entered the start and endpoints as 1e-1 and 1e3 in np.logspace it gives that error as the number is too large for python to handle. Instead use -1 and 3 as the start and end points in the logspace function. </p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'HW7 Problem 2 Part 4 inhomogenous array', 'timestamp': '2023-03-25T00:59:35Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 91}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>I&#39;m trying to work on find_distinctive_ngrams, but my output is slightly off from the given values (&#39;lecs/1_vidText.txt&#39;: [&#39;econ&#39;, &#39;seco&#39;, &#39;pers&#39;], &#39;lecs/2_vidText.txt&#39;: [&#39;uter&#39;, &#39;sspo&#39;, &#39;oint&#39;]). I figured that&#39;s the problem because the third ngram has the exact same tfidf value with the one after. In this case, how should I solve the problem? </p> Answer: <div><p>Probably you are missing out on sorting the keys, prior to preparing the doc word matrix.</p></div><p></p><p></p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'HW8 Q2 same tfidf value in find_distinctive_ngrams', 'timestamp': '2023-03-25T00:42:06Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 2, 'views': 136}),
