	Document(content="""Question: <div>I currently have </div><pre>    r = re.compile(&#39;([A-Z][a-z]&#43;)? ([A-Z][a-z]&#43;) rides a ([A-Za-z]&#43;)? ([A-Za-z]*)&#39;)    f = re.compile(&#39;([A-Z][a-z]&#43;)? ([A-Z][a-z]&#43;) flies a ([A-Za-z]&#43;)? ([A-Za-z]*)&#39;)</pre><div>However, for some reason, it only selects two words and not one or two words?</div><div></div><div>How should I fix this to select one or two words</div> Answer: You currently have it set up so that the first word may or may not appear, which makes reasonable sense. However, if there is only a single word, you appear to start your pattern with a space. Hopefully this helps you identify how to fix your issue.""", meta={'folders': ['hw6'], 'title': 'One or Two words', 'timestamp': '2023-03-03T06:19:36Z', 'user': 'jzhjvtza66q373', 'tags': ['hw6', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 19}),
