	Document(content="""Question: <p>How do I get around this problem of the re.sub replacing the whole string from my pattern? Since the pattern is searching for boy/girl followed by a capital lettered word? </p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fl8au962mr8x6og%2F8fef6ed678e319c350fc20e4037ef763911fa66c31649b626476cdc41c3483fd%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p> Answer: <md>Look into regex “groups” in the lecture notes if you haven’t already. If you can divide the detected string into the hero’s name and “Boy”/“Girl”, you can keep the original name and replace only the “Boy”/“Girl” part.One approach might be to create a new string like `replacement_string = original_name + “ Man”`, and use that during replacement.</md>""", meta={'folders': ['hw6'], 'title': 'HW 6 Prob 3', 'timestamp': '2023-03-03T01:08:36Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw6', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 138}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>Which grade will be used to calculate our final grade? The one on Brightspace or the one on Gradescope? Does the one on Gradescope matter?</p> Answer: The Brightspace grade (post-curve grade) is used to calculate the final grade.""", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Exam 1 Grade', 'timestamp': '2023-03-01T23:28:30Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 245}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fl8au6tk8ajv2s9%2F3e81cc4db356b9a7b66d1f52068085341d9ff1a8643ec1abff0e4bba11c360c4%2Fimage.png' alt='image.pngNaN' /></p><p>Due to the curve, I got an overflowing score on Exam 1, but the total score for exams shows 50/50. Will my extra score be counted in the calculation of the final grade of the course? I want to make sure so that I can account for it in my calculations for my grade.</p><p>Thank you.</p> Answer: <p>Yes, you will keep the extra score. </p>""", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Grade Overflow on Exam 1', 'timestamp': '2023-03-01T23:13:27Z', 'user': 'l8au6tk8ajv2s9', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 24}),
	Document(content="""Note: <p>Hello All!<br /><br />Exam 1 scores are now available on both Gradescope and Brightspace. You can log in to either platform to check your score.<br /><br />Please note that the points assigned to you on Gradescope and Brightspace are not the same. This is because the points have been curved. The final grade on Brightspace will reflect the curved score, whereas the Gradescope score reflects the original score before the curve.<br /><br />If you have any concerns about your score, you can put in a <b style='font-style:normal'>regrade request on Gradescope</b>. Please note that the deadline for regrade requests is one week from today (03/01). If you miss this deadline, we will not be able to consider your request.<br /><br />We encourage you to review your exam and use the solutions provided in the Exam 1 module (on Brightspace) to improve your understanding of the material. If you have any questions or concerns about your score or the exam, please do not hesitate to reach out to us.<br /><br /></p>""", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Exam 1 Scores Released!', 'timestamp': '2023-03-01T21:09:17Z', 'user': 'kskmx82xa2s4ad', 'tags': ['exam', 'instructor-note'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 266}),
