	Document(content="""Question: <p>For HW 6 Problem 2, I am searching for groups in regex. I got my statement to match what was required so that the correct string ___ rides/flies a ___ matched for all the test cases. I put parenthesies around each group and compiled the pattern. I then searched the string using the syntax result = b.search(searchstring).group(1) but it says there is a &#34;nonetype&#34; so there is no group. When I use the fullmatch function, the correct groups are matched. How would I get these groups out of the matched product? Thank you</p> Answer: Resolved """, meta={'folders': ['hw6'], 'title': 'Groups in Regex', 'timestamp': '2023-03-01T16:27:00Z', 'user': 'l6maptmggzy7op', 'tags': ['hw6', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 15}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>If the string is </p><pre>&#34;Spider boy and Spider girl&#34;</pre><p>should we replace both &#34;boy&#34; and &#34;girl&#34; so it becomes</p><pre>&#34;Spider Man and Spider Women&#34;</pre><p></p><p>If so, how do we return both instances if match and search can only return the first occurrence?</p> Answer: <p>*Woman not Women, but yes, you should. Why wouldn&#39;t you?</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw6'], 'title': 'HW6 Problem 3 multiple subsitutions', 'timestamp': '2023-02-28T16:32:24Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw6', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 155}),
