	Document(content="""Question: <p>I was trying to install scipy but my computer (a windows computer using Linux) is saying that it cannot find a module named pip. Is there something I am mistyping?</p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb4af56794cp%2F4dc3cfff4826b2c9a92b60c1cde192f7edc77061d34efed85223a57c65b780ff%2FScreenshot_2023-01-30_212018.png' width='972' height='68' alt='' /></p> Answer: <p>Adding on to the student answer for visibility - <br />If you have a fresh installation of Python, try -</p><pre><code>sudo apt-get install python3-pip</code></pre><p></p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'Trouble installing scipy', 'timestamp': '2023-01-31T03:21:00Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 129}),
	Document(content="""Note: <p>Hi!<br /><br />We have noticed a lot of questions in the @student channel in the course&#39;s discord. The place to ask questions and that TAs monitor is Piazza, so if you are looking for answer to a question, piazza is the place to look and ask (there were several times questions in the @student_channel were already answered on Piazza). Although we will keep the student_channel in the discord, please know that TAs will not be monitoring if for questions (though TAs still be hosting office hours on Discord, that does not change!!!).<br /><br /><br /></p>""", meta={'folders': ['logistics'], 'title': 'Questions on Piazza vs Questions in #student_channel in Discord', 'timestamp': '2023-01-31T02:53:22Z', 'user': 'kskmxecspaq4i1', 'tags': ['instructor-note', 'logistics'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 122}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>I am unsure of how I can access and compare the years when one of them is already combined into the dict. I keep getting a key error when messing around with indexes to access it. </p> Answer: Before adding a new individual to the dictionary, you should be able to check on those already added. <div><br /></div><div>Your keys in the return dictionary should be months of people already added to the dictionary. </div><div><br /></div>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'For homework 2 problem 2, how do I compare the birthdays before combine', 'timestamp': '2023-01-31T00:14:27Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 113}),
