	Document(content="""Question: <p>I tried both commands in the terminal to install the python module for hw 3, and both times it says the command is not found. I have a windows. What could be the error? Is there another command I can try?</p> Answer: Can you include a screenshot of what you commanded and the error? And did you find anything potentially useful when googling the error? """, meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'installing python module for hw 3 not working', 'timestamp': '2023-01-30T18:46:28Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 132}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>In the section before the Instructions, val1 stores the X and Y coordinates, but what does val2 store?</p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fksi8k0dd7bh6fe%2Fab4a280ee2eee5d3e54a8d27eb05619bb4519b0b19ed4f0068a2ee479039c12f%2Fimage.png' alt='image.pngNaN' width='578' height='242' /></p> Answer: Tuple of LSRL parameters""", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'HW03 Instructions', 'timestamp': '2023-01-30T16:09:38Z', 'user': 'ksi8k0dd7bh6fe', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 145}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>For the sweep_n function in Problem 1, should we round the j_values in the output list to 4 decimal places? (It is shown here rounded, but not stated directly in the instructions.)</p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fksi8ka1ba1t6tv%2F22d7fbafa238fc01eae9ad3ec9e70c817a01a3b54031698621d6b092dae51e79%2Fimage.png' alt='image.pngNaN' /></p> Answer: You should not round to four decimal places — the readme merely shows four places so that you can more easily compare your results. The grading will also only check four decimal places.""", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'HW3 Problem 1.3', 'timestamp': '2023-01-30T15:37:10Z', 'user': 'ksi8ka1ba1t6tv', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 150}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>Hello,<br /><br />Whenever I try to run my solution for hw3 problem 1, I get this error (see picture). I looked at @82 to see if that could solve anything, but I am not on a Mac (I am on Windows), and have also already tried the recommendations in that question and none of them have worked. I also only get this problem for matplotlib and not for scipy or numpy, between problem 1 and problem 2. Would anyone be able to help with this? Thank you in advance!!<br /><br /><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb885y1s32ee%2F7ff57fb96556c85fadb749c42666fa117af25e790c374af29e9cb58585a9a881%2Fimage.png' alt='image.pngNaN' width='598' height='191' /></p> Answer: <p>If you have installed multiple versions of python, that could happen. The module is installed on a python version that is not default to be called. To check all python versions and the defualt (in terminal), type py -0p in your terminal (this only works for Windows.). And your IDE and terminal could run different python versions as the default. If you want to check the version used by your IDE, go to the tab &#34;Environment&#34; or something similar.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'Matplotlib Import Error', 'timestamp': '2023-01-30T05:19:18Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 136}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>Do we have to use matplotlib to generate the histogram? I used np.histogram instead, and it produces the correct results from my testing, but I&#39;m not sure if using np.histogram will affect grading.</p> Answer: <p>np.histogram is a function that makes numeric result, which gives you an array. matplotlib  is a module to generate graphs.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw3'], 'title': 'HW 3 Problem 2 Matplotlib Use', 'timestamp': '2023-01-30T00:35:11Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw3', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 154}),
	Document(content="""Question: I found a very serious problem with my hw2 q2. That, I finished the hw2 question 2 that fulfill the Requirement on instructions in GitHub, which would return both “bob” and “John” with same month. Since the instructions in GitHub wasn’t changed, and I didn’t notice the announcement in piazza until today. Could I have a extension of hw2 or could you please grade my hw2 question2 based on instructions and test cases shown in GitHub?  Answer: <p>I will contact the GTA of the course and they will update the class with an answer. Thank you for letting us know.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'Problem with homework 2 question 2', 'timestamp': '2023-01-29T07:30:18Z', 'user': 'k83r1oihjvd2uq', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 127}),
