	Document(content="""Question: <p>I&#39;m having an issue where this specific test case is the only one not working, and every other test case is fine. this test case just outputs a list with 0s in it. Does anyone have a similar issue?<img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb5gx345d2ba%2Fe11fa02ab4fa2291635d8c06421c4454f43017f1de0b59e8ca4320a930698a87%2FScreen_Shot_2023-01-27_at_11.49.36_AM.png' alt='Screen_Shot_2023-01-27_at_11.49.36_AM.pngNaN' /></p> Answer: <p>resolved, but used a redundant solution</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'hw2 p1', 'timestamp': '2023-01-27T16:51:22Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 97}),
	Document(content="""Question: <ol dir='auto'><li><p dir='auto'>Ignore any values in <code>data</code> that are less than or equal to <code>min_val</code> and greater than or equal to <code>max_val</code>. *Remember if you have changed <code>max_val</code> and &#39;min_val&#39; in step 3, you would need to work with the new value of <code>max_val</code> and <code>min_val</code>.</p></li></ol><p></p><p>^what is meant by ignore? like make that value =0?</p> Answer: <p>Don&#39;t count that value as a &#34;count&#34; in your &#34;histogram.&#34;</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'hw2 prob1', 'timestamp': '2023-01-27T16:02:23Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 104}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>Since custom test case files aren&#39;t graded and it would be a good practice to keep all of our work updated in the repository, I would think it&#39;s encouraged to push custom test case files. However, I also considered that the auto-grader may conflict with unexpected files in the repository? I would be glad to know either way. </p> Answer: <p>Custom test case files such as ones you create yourself? In that case there is no need to push them, but you can if you would like.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'Should we push custom test case files?', 'timestamp': '2023-01-26T22:51:00Z', 'user': 'ktnb7c2eqqn5ky', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 130}),
