	Document(content="""Question: <p>I currently have 0 in for homework, is that because the homework hasn&#39;t been graded yet? </p> Answer: When a homework is graded, you should see a post about it on Piazza. Additionally, there will be a graded tab on your HW repository with feedback on your grade and how it was calculated. If you see a zero in Brightspace, but nothing on GitHub or Piazza, I would assume it has not yet been graded.<div><br /></div><div>Grading usually takes around a week. Should your homework be graded but your Brightspace does not reflect the grade on GitHub, or you have any other grading issue, please file a regrade request.</div>""", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Homework 1 Grades', 'timestamp': '2023-01-26T04:42:47Z', 'user': 'ktnb5cdi52e1o5', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 194}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>Hi,</p><p>I&#39;m not sure why, but now I&#39;m not being able to use git add command now. It&#39;s telling me that my directories are wrong. But for homework 1 I did the same thing and put the files in the same location and it worked. <img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fl74llwu85zn4nq%2Fd8bb042293fd09398c83f5b022ad83297ecd3e1141b88f9cecd79327832ef7b6%2FScreenshot_2023-01-25_221354.png' width='1008' height='163' alt='I had this showed up but cannot use git add to add the file for commit' /></p> Answer: From looking at this screenshot alone, it seems you are trying to git commit before doing git add, although I could be wrong. If this does not resolve your issue, I’d recommend attending office hours so a TA can troubleshoot more effectively.""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'Unable to push local file to github', 'timestamp': '2023-01-26T03:16:24Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 18}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>When I tried insert the bin width as a range I get this message &#34; &lt;built-in function range&gt;&#34; instead of the actual numbers.</p> Answer: Range is a key word that creates an array of values.<div>Range (0,4) = [0,1,2,3]</div><div>You are likely trying to use the function range inappropriately and are getting your error.</div><div>If you are trying to find the bin values you may instead want to use two separate float values for the maximum and minimum of the histogram bounds.</div>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'hw2 Q1', 'timestamp': '2023-01-25T18:58:51Z', 'user': 'lcrzmj6nzh1w6', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 146}),
