	Document(content="""Question: <p>Hello, just when trying to create a blank/basic plot for prob 1 hw 2 my program compiles however no plot window is generated instead just the phrase none is generated and nothing else. </p><p></p><p>For reference running ubuntu lts 22.04,</p><p></p><p>how can i get the plot window to appear?</p> Answer: <p>For problem 1 on homework 2, you shouldn&#39;t have to create a plot. Instead just a list of all the bins with the frequencies of each bin. The list will be the histogram.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'plot not showing up - &#34;none instead&#34;', 'timestamp': '2023-01-21T19:03:55Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 151}),
	Document(content="""Note: <div>Hi all,<br />We apologize for the confusion from our end. <b>Please ignore the commented expected outputs in testbirthday1.py and testbirthday2.py</b>:<br /><br /><b>Clarification 1:</b><br />The following should be the expected output of <b>testbirthday1.py</b></div><pre>{1: (&#39;John&#39;, (15, 1985, 37)), 2: (&#39;Jane&#39;, (20, 1989, 33))}</pre><div>Expected output for <b>testbirthday2.py:</b></div><pre>{3: (&#39;Alice&#39;, (2, 1980, 42)), 4: (&#39;Bob&#39;, (3, 1970, 52))}</pre><div>If two people have the same month, only the person who is <b>OLDER (in terms of age)</b>, should be included.<br />For example, if we have:</div><pre>person_to_day = {&#39;Tom&#39;: 25, &#39;Jerry&#39;: 30}person_to_month = {&#39;Tom&#39;: 8, &#39;Jerry&#39;: 8}person_to_year = {&#39;Tom&#39;: 1975, &#39;Jerry&#39;: 1980}</pre><div>The expected output should be:</div><pre>{8: (&#39;Tom&#39;, (25, 1975, 47))}</pre><div>Since, &#39;Tom&#39; is older than &#39;Jerry&#39;<b>.<br /><br /></b><b>Note 1: If the order of the dictionary&#39;s key:values don&#39;t match to the given output, then it is acceptable. However all the key:value pair should be there.</b><br /><b><br />Note 2: For Problem 2, you need to calculate age using the year 2022</b>.<br /><br /><b>Clarification 2:</b><br />Here we provide the test cases outputs for <b>Problem 1.</b><br />Expected output for <b>testhisto1.py</b>:</div><pre>[0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 2, 0, 1, 0]</pre><div>Expected output for <b>testhisto2.py</b>:</div><pre>[0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 0]</pre><div>Expected output for <b>testhisto3.py</b>:</div><pre>[0, 0, 3]</pre><div>Expected output for <b>testhisto4.py</b>:</div><pre>[0, 0, 0, 0, 0]</pre><div><b><br />Clarification 3:</b><br /><b>How to run view the test cases output? (in Linux):</b></div><ol><li>Make sure you are in the right folder where your homework2.py is located.</li><li>You could open the terminal, and simply type.</li></ol><div></div><pre>python3 testbirthday1.py</pre><div>Similarly, you could run the other python files, <b>testbirthday2.py, testhisto1.py, testhisto2.py, testhisto3.py, testhisto4.py</b> and check your output and match it with the given output.<br />Lastly, Please let us know if you have anymore questions regarding HW2 (on Piazza or during OH.)<br /><br /></div>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'Homework 2 Clarifications', 'timestamp': '2023-01-21T18:01:38Z', 'user': 'ksla74foumq7mf', 'tags': ['hw2', 'instructor-note'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 360}),
