	Document(content="""Question: <p>For the expected output, should there be two parentheses even though there&#39;s only one item in the dictionary? And should there be quotations for the month in keys? </p><p></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb6lxjfnn105%2Fd8dbd168076ec41ae856479dc0383685fedeb209bba86a4fafd58cd9ccf02129%2FScreenshot_2023-01-20_at_2.33.38_PM.png' alt='Screenshot_2023-01-20_at_2.33.38_PM.png' /></p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fktnb6lxjfnn105%2F143e8abe577d4ab72e1d617b81be35e12e61af7aaee46ea988db9780d1267aa8%2FScreenshot_2023-01-20_at_2.34.04_PM.png' alt='Screenshot_2023-01-20_at_2.34.04_PM.png' /></p> Answer: <p>I believe @51 addresses your question</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'Test birthday expected output confusion', 'timestamp': '2023-01-20T19:36:29Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 6, 'views': 138}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>How do we know if we passed the test for the histogram test cases? Are there expected outputs? </p> Answer: <p>Sorry about the confusion - the outputs (along with other HW02 clarifications) should now be in @51.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'How to verify histogram test cases', 'timestamp': '2023-01-20T19:03:04Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 146}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>expected answer in the hw2 testbirthday 2, the last item in the dictionary is missing a closing parenthesis. Also, since we are working with nested tuples, single elements will have a comma afterward. This is not reflected in the expected answers in the test files. Is it fine if ours has a comma? Also if we use default_dict to wrap tuples, when printed it will have an indicator of what type it is when the dictionary is printed, is this also fine?</p><p>output:</p><p><img src='/redirect/s3?bucket=uploads&amp;prefix=paste%2Fky3mk36vi794uu%2Fbec7cc15bd2a1b56d487b2ee235fc4a71968894be12240b5e35319a9b6a3f06e%2Fimage.png' alt='image.png' /></p><p></p><p>Also why is there no expected answers for the histogram test files?</p> Answer: <p>The missing parentheses is likely a mistake. There is a way to avoid the comma in the tuples. I basically added a condition to check for the length of the data for a month, then either converted to a tuple from a list (if there were multiple elements), or just took the data from list[0] (which is the single tuple element) and re-assigned it to the correct month. </p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'expected hw ans', 'timestamp': '2023-01-20T18:45:44Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 143}),
	Document(content="""Question: <p>On HW2 it says to calculate age using the year 2022, is this correct or do we need to change the year to 2023?</p> Answer: <p>You have to calculate age using the year 2022 itself.</p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'Clarification on HW2', 'timestamp': '2023-01-20T17:28:32Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 3, 'views': 146}),
	Document(content="""Note: <p>Hi Class!</p><p>Homework 2 has been released on GitHub classroom. Please use the link in the post to accept the assignment and get started with the homework for the course. Note that Homework 2 is due on the 27th of January at 11:59pm. Moreover, you can also take benefit of the TA lab hours (in-person and virtual) to get help for the current and all future homeworks. <br /><br /></p><p>Homework 2: <a href='https://classroom.github.com/a/4Qi0RjRo'>https://classroom.github.com/a/4Qi0RjRo</a><br />*Follow the link, you will get access to the homework. The homework will provide instructions on how to submit the homework. This class does not have the students added the github classroom. <strong>Use the same github account that you documented in the git hub user google form survey! </strong></p><p></p><p dir='ltr'>TA Lab Hours Info:<br />Virtual lab hours (Discord): T-F 9-11 am ET, 1-2 pm ET, and 5-8 pm ET. Discord link: <a href='https://discord.gg/vU94QaeacS'><strong>https://discord.gg/vU94QaeacS</strong></a></p><p dir='ltr'>Limited in-person lab hours (maximum of 10 people per half hour slot) :<br />BHEE 206(primary - go here first) &amp; 207 (overflow) T-F 5pm-8pm ET </p><p dir='ltr'></p><p dir='ltr'></p>""", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'H2 Released', 'timestamp': '2023-01-20T16:50:24Z', 'user': 'ksla74foumq7mf', 'tags': ['hw2', 'instructor-note'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 292}),
